text: Drew County is a county of the U.S. state of Arkansas. As of the 2020 census, the population was 17,350. The county seat and largest city is Monticello. Drew County was founded on November 26, 1846, and named for Thomas Drew, the third governor of Arkansas. == References == Category:1840s establishments in Arkansas Category:1846 establishments in the United States Category:Arkansas counties
title: Drew County, Arkansas
